nd maintaining a registered office address in the BVI.</span></li><li id="i24rnu2"><span id="imoaysx"><strong>CIGA (Core Income-Generating Activities) Test:</strong> The Offshore company must engage in a set of business activities that generate its primary income within the BVI territory.</span></li></ol><p id="ikogfi5"><strong>Note:</strong> It&#039;s crucial to note that failure to submit the Economic Substance Report in compliance with BVI government regulations can lead to severe consequences, including company closure. Non-compliance with reporting deadlines may result in a maximum fine of $200,000 USD. </p></div><div id="imhncr-1" role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane fade"><p id="i7efhiz">For Belize Companies Economic Substance Law requires you to: </p><ol t4-container="" t4-bid="core_element_basic_order-list" t4-group="Element" id="iizac3j" class="order-list"><li id="iaupeqh"><span><strong>Demonstrate CIGA Activities:</strong> Prove that the activities responsible for generating the primary source of income for the Offshore company occur in Belize.</span></li><li id="i3efzbl"><span><strong>Show Presence in Belize:</strong> Provide evidence of the company&#039;s presence in Belize, including the number of Board of Directors meetings held in Belize, with recording strategic decisions in meeting minutes, maintaining records and minutes in Belize, and demonstrating the knowledge and expertise of the board of directors in fulfilling their duties.</span></li></ol><p id="iv1o1pb"><strong>Note:</strong> Failure to submit the report on the nature of business activities in accordance with Belize government laws can result in administrative fines ranging from 150,000 to 300,000 Belizean dollars. Additionally, it may lead to the suspension, revocation of the business license, or removal from the Belize Business Register. </p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><div id="i2s7js" class="t4b-box"><p id="ior0ik">How to complete your annual requirements with e